that chinese has a word for ten thousand, wàn (万), and thus for example 50,000 becomes wu wan, not wu shi qian. nearly all present-day chinese coins and bills a lot of chinese currency will be in the form of bills — even small change. bills are more common in some areas, coins in others, but both are accepted anywhere. even the jiao, at just one tenth of a yuan, exists as both a bill (the smallest) and two different coins. conversely, one yuan exists both as a coin and as two different bills. you should be prepared to recognize 